e/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 345, \"end\": 356, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 2024 Olympics will begin on July 26 and, for the first time in history, the parade of athletes will take place outside the main stadium, in boats on the river.\", \"from\": 443, \"to\": 606, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite this innovation, there were concerns over security, especially after the terrorist attacks in Moscow last month.\", \"from\": 607, \"to\": 727, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 709, \"end\": 715, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\", \"score\": 0.9999717169769375, \"rank\": 2.1758241459972185e-05, \"text\": \"Moscow\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France has raised its terrorist alert warning to its highest level.\", \"from\": 728, \"to\": 795, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 728, \"end\": 734, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9965423386451119, \"rank\": 0.0017677901874359654, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Earlier this week, French President Emmanuel Macron and the country's Sports Minister Amelie Oudea-Castera announced the opening ceremony for Paris 2024 will not be relocated from the Seine.\", \"from\": 797, \"to\": 987, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 816, \"end\": 832, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French President\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\"}, {\